Make utmost effort to achieve a more in depth, complete physical count of all PPEs of the Municipality and submit the same within the prescribed period;

Require the GSO and the Municipal Accountant to maintain an updated Property Cards and Property Ledger Cards, respectively, per category on all PPE 	as recorded in the books of accounts, ensure the maintenance of the same for the recent years’ procurements and continuously work on the previous acquisitions; and

Require both offices to reconcile property records with the accounting records and adjust the books of accounts and the property records, as warranted, after reconciliation.

Utilize the unexpended LDDRMF for PPAs that would help mitigate and reduce the impact and/or effects of calamities and adversities that may befall the Municipality;

Direct the attention of the Municipal Engineer to evaluate the true cause/s of the discontinuance/suspension of the construction during the previous 	administration, and take immediate and appropriate actions;

Compel the contractor to resume the operations and complete the projects; and

For the succeeding LDRRM projects, take appropriate action, legal or otherwise, to compel the contractor to complete the projects in due time.

Instruct the LDRRM Officer to promptly submit the monthly Report on the Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF on or before the 15th day after the end of each month pursuant to the procedures of the aforecited Circular, to facilitate verification  thereof;

Comply with the monthly Report on the Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF for the CY 2020 that were not submitted; and

Take appropriate actions in facilitating and monitoring the preparation and submission of the required monthly reports for the timely evaluation and validations of the disbursements from the fund.

